Mobile Artificial Intelligence (AI) technology can be segmented based on components, technologies, and applications. In terms of components, the market is divided into hardware and software solutions. Hardware components include processors and other physical components, while software encompasses algorithms and applications that enable AI functionalities on mobile devices. The technology segment includes machine learning, natural language processing, and computer vision, which are integral parts of bringing AI capabilities to mobile platforms. Additionally, AI in mobile finds applications across smartphones, wearables, automotive systems, and various other sectors, showcasing its versatility and growing adoption across different industries.

